OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FFootball phone-in pioneer  
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25FTony Butler dies           
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Tony Butler, the man widely credited   
OL,6, with inventing the radio football      
OL,7, phone-in in England, has died aged 88. 
OL,9,FThe radio legend's forthright and      
OL,10,Fdistinctive style made him one of the  
OL,11,Fearly stars on local radio.            
OL,13,FButler worked at one of the UK's first 
OL,14,Fcommercial stations, Birmingham's BRMB,
OL,15,Fin the 1970s.                          
OL,17,FTributes have been paid to the "larger 
OL,18,Fthan life" character, with BBC Radio   
OL,19,FWM's Daz Hale saying "he was a giant"  
OL,20,Fin broadcasting.                       
